---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Who maintains Qazaq Lens, why it exists and what its limitations are.">
  <article class="wrap article-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p><h1>About Qazaq Lens</h1>
    <div class="article-body">
      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>Stereotypes about Kazakhstan travel faster than context. Qazaq Lens creates short, linkable explanations for international readers who want to distinguish comedy, shorthand and assumptions from sourced information about a real country.</p>
      <h2>Who runs it</h2>
      <p>The project is currently maintained by one person. It is not a government project, tourism campaign or newsroom. That limitation is stated openly because a solo editor can miss context that a diverse editorial team would catch.</p>
      <h2>What it does not claim</h2>
      <p>Qazaq Lens does not speak for Kazakhstan's government, every citizen, every ethnic community or every Kazakh person abroad. It also does not treat criticism of Kazakhstan as automatically false. The project addresses specific checkable claims and labels interpretation separately.</p>
      <h2>How trust is earned</h2>
      <p>Every substantial article exposes its claim ledger, source IDs, review status, last source-review date and change history. Public-beta material is not presented as independently reviewed.</p>
      <h2>Contact and corrections</h2>
      <p>Use the <a href="/report-error">correction form</a> to report a factual error, a weak source, missing context or unfair wording.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
